Aim:
To understand how tuples work in Python and perform some basic operations on them.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Create a tuple with some elements.
Display the tuple.
Find the length of the tuple.
Access and display an element using its index.
Count how many times an element appears in the tuple.
Find the index position of a specific element.
Display all the results.
End the program.

Code:
t = (10, 20, 30, 20, 40)
print("Tuple:", t)
print("Length of tuple:", len(t))
print("Element at index 2:", t[2])
print("Count of 20:", t.count(20))
print("Index of 30:", t.index(30))

Output:
Tuple: (10, 20, 30, 20, 40)
Length of tuple: 5
Element at index 2: 30
Count of 20: 2
Index of 30: 2
